flowRoot.flowPara: When a transfer is done you'll get a notification to be able to act upon it.
If Transfers is closed during a running transfer, you'll get a icon in the message tray with the currently running transfers.
When all the transfers are done the tray icon should go away.
Reveals in Files with the file selected and ready to be acted upon (open, move etc.)
If it shall be kept or not depends on if we can trust apps to have a way from the view mode to the edit mode of say, a document.
Working from the idea that the social context is more important than the type of file you get when sending things to someone over chat.
